ChatGPT vs. Google Search :

A lot of people think that these 2 are the same thing. But honestly they aren’t. They are built differently.
Google Search looks for things on the internet that already exist. It is like a tool that helps you find things.
ChatGPT generates text based on things it has learned. It’s aim is to generate.
If you search on Google for a pasta recipe, it will show you pages that have that recipe. If you ask ChatGPT for the pasta recipe, it will make a recipe for you based on lots of other recipes it has seen.
I don’t think one is better, than the other. Google Search is good when you need to know something that’s true right now. ChatGPT is often used when you need something explained or summarized

Does it understands you?
I want you to register this in your head. ChatGPT doesn’t understand language the way we do. What it has is a detailed statistical map of how human language works.
When we ask a question, it recognizes the pattern of your words and generates a response that statistically fits a correct response. This is because it has seen millions of examples of humans asking and answering similar questions.
It seems as if GPT understands. But honestly speaking, it’s a very different process than what happens in your mind. It’s an extreme pattern matching model.

ChatGPT is a program that generates text. That’s the simplest definition that I can ever give you. When you give text as input, it gives you text as output. It’s amazing at what it does and that’s because it’s built using large language model.
So the word GPT stands for Generative Pre-trained Transformer. In very simple words, let’s understand this.
Generative means it generates new content.
Pre-trained means it has learned from a massive amount of text before having a conversation with you.
Transformer is the name of the architecture that powers it.
OpenAI is the company that came up with ChatGPT. You need to realize that GPT isn’t a database or a search engine. Yes it responses to your queries. But it’s a model that generates responses word by word. These responses are generated based on the patterns GPT has learned during it’s training.
